üìö Literature Text Analyzer

This Python script is a command-line tool designed to assist with literary analysis. It combines a natural language processing (NLP) library (TextBlob) with the power of OpenAI's GPT models to provide insights into a specific quote from Frederick Douglass's Narrative of the Life of Frederick Douglass, an American Slave.

The program performs three key functions:

    Quote Verification: Checks if a user-provided quote exists within a specified PDF of the text.

    AI-Powered Explanation: Sends the quote to the OpenAI API to generate a detailed, literary-focused explanation.

    Sentiment Analysis: Uses the TextBlob library to perform a quick diagnostic, providing a sentiment (polarity and subjectivity) analysis of the quote.

üõ†Ô∏è Requirements

To run this script, you will need to install the necessary Python packages and set up your OpenAI API key.
Python Packages

Install the required libraries using pip:

pip install openai python-dotenv textblob PyPDF2

API Key

This project requires an OpenAI API key to function. To keep your key secure, you must use a .env file.

    Create a file named .env in the same directory as the Lit_Project.py script.

    Add your API key to this file in the following format:

    OPENAI_API_KEY='your_actual_openai_api_key_here'

    Replace 'your_actual_openai_api_key_here' with your real API key.

üöÄ How to Use

    Place Your PDF: Ensure that the PDF file for Narrative of the Life of Frederick Douglass, an American Slave is located at the path specified in the script. The current hardcoded path is:

    /run/media/darklord/GVH USB/Python Code/Douglass_Narrative.pdf

    You may need to update this path in the main() function to match the location of your file.

    Run the Script: Open your terminal and navigate to the directory containing the script. Then, execute the script with the following command:

    python Lit_Project.py

    Enter Your Quote: The program will prompt you to enter a quote from the text. Type or paste the quote and press Enter.

The script will then output the following:

    A confirmation of whether the quote was found in the PDF.

    An explanation of the quote generated by OpenAI.

    A sentiment analysis of the quote.

    A hardcoded MLA citation for the book.

